Institutional
Since Profit Investments was established in 1996, our flagship products have been our composite portfolios serving institutional clients. We have a long and solid track record managing large-cap, small-cap and socially responsible portfolios. Profit Investments is a Registered Investment Advisor.
Large-Cap Equity

Fund Facts



Stocks
42-65 Stocks


Turnover
<45% Turnover


Inception Date
10/31/97





Overview
The Profit Large Cap Equity portfolio seeks to provide investors with a high, long-term total return, consistent with the preservation of capital and maintenance of liquidity by investing primarily in the common stock of established, larger capitalization companies. Profit Large Cap Equity is benchmarked to the Russell 1000 Growth and Russell 1000 Indexes.





Small-Cap Equity

Fund Facts



Stocks
38-65 Stocks


Turnover
< 12% Turnover


Inception Date
03/31/05





Overview
The Profit Small Cap Equity portfolio seeks to provide investors with long-term capital appreciation by investing primarily in the common stock of established small capitalization companies. The Profit Small Cap Equity is benchmarked to the Russell 2000 Growth and Russell 2000 Indexes.





Environmental, Social & Governance Equity (ESG)

Fund Facts



Stocks
42-65 Stocks


Turnover
< 4% Turnover


Inception Date
11/04/02





Overview
The Profit Social Equity portfolio seeks to provide investors with a high, long-term total return, consistent with the preservation of capital and maintenance of liquidity by investing primarily in the common stock of established, larger capitalization companies which have passed social screens of reputable socially screening research firms. The Profit ESG Equity is benchmarked to the R1000, R1000 Growth and the MSCI KLD 400 ETF Indexes.






For information regarding our  institutional products, email: jfeeley@profitfunds.com

 

 


